==English==
===Etymology===
The term was coined in May 1998 by Chiew Lee Yih (赵里昱) from Malaysia, who used it first in newsgroups. Almost simultaneously, Chen Lan coined it for use in the Western media based on the term tàikōng (太空), Chinese for space. ''(Source: [[w:Astronaut|Astronaut]] at Wikipedia)''
===Noun===
'''taikonaut'''
# a person who travels in space for the Chinese space program; a Chinese [[astronaut]]

